# Architecture Decision Records (ADR)

Capture context, decision, and consequences of significant technical choices. Prevents re-litigating settled decisions.

## When to Write

| Trigger | Template |
|---|---|
| DB, framework, API style, cloud provider, new microservice | MADR Full |
| Linter rules, minor tooling | MADR Minimal |
| One-sentence justification | Y-Statement |
| Config typo, dependency patch | Skip |

**Rule:** Decision affects team >6 months → write ADR.

## 3 Templates

**MADR Full** (frontmatter: status/date/decision-makers/consulted/informed):
- Context and Problem Statement
- Decision Drivers
- Considered Options (≥3 including "do nothing")
- Decision Outcome + Consequences (good AND bad)
- Pros and Cons per option
- Confirmation (how to verify + when to revisit)

**MADR Minimal:** Context → Decision → Consequences (good/bad/mitigation)

**Y-Statement:** `In context of X, facing Y, we decided Z against A/B, to achieve C, accepting D.`

## Lifecycle
`Proposed → Accepted → Deprecated / Superseded by ADR-NNNN`

Never edit Accepted ADRs. Create a new one that supersedes.

## Directory
`docs/adr/NNNN-kebab-title.md` + `docs/adr/README.md` (index table)

## Anti-Patterns
- One option only → document all considered options with pros/cons
- No consequences → be honest about bad outcomes
- Editing Accepted ADR → create superseding ADR instead
- ADR for trivial decisions → use minimal template or skip
- Perpetual Proposed → set 2-week decision deadline

## Ecosystem
- `c4-model` → ADRs document WHY behind C4 L2 container choices
- `ddd-core` → ADRs capture subdomain classification decisions
- `why-strategic-rationale` → ADR = technical implementation of WHY Statement
- `evolutionary-architecture` → ADRs track architectural dimension decisions
